<title>USA: After merging, refiners must look at closing plant.</title>
<headline>After merging, refiners must look at closing plant.</headline>
<byline>David Chance</byline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-06-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>The spate of mergers and ventures in the U.S. refining industry will achieve little unless capacity is actually cut, say industry specialists.</p>
<p>So far, capacity closures have hit smaller, less efficient refineries and while 30 units with around a million barrels per day have been closed since 1992, new technology and the desire to spread fixed costs with higher product runs means that output has risen.</p>
